"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The use of `reset_index(drop=True)` on the result of `apply` is incorrect because it does not align the resulting Series with the original DataFrame's index. This can lead to misalignment of the new column 'z' with the DataFrame 'df'.\",\n  \"patch\": \"9c9\\n< df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).reset_index(drop=True)\\n---\\n> df['z'] = df.groupby(['y']).apply(lambda x: (x['x1'] != x['x1'].shift(-1)) | (x['x2'] != x['x2'].shift(-1))).reset_index(level=0, drop=True)\"\n}"